M. KANANACK & CO., Inc., Meyer Kananack and Irving Kananack, Plaintiffs in Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error.* (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 15, 1926.) No. 196. John B. Johnston, of New York City (Vine H. Smith and Lazarus Joseph, both of New York City, of counsel, and Jacob S. Demov, of New York City, on the brief), for plaintiffs in error. Emory R. Buckner, U. S. Atty., of New York City (David P. Siegel, William J. Millard, and Raphael Koenig, Asst. U. S. Attys., all of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MANTON, Circuit Judges.

Certiorari denied 46 S. Ct. 633, 70 L. Ed. —.

 PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
